---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QuickSummary from '../components/QuickSummary.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Squad Building" 
  description="Core principles for building strong squads in Last War: Survival — Main Squad First, mono-type rules, positioning, Monica, and when to diversify."
>
  <h1>Squad Building</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-[#8a96b0]">Core concepts and principles that apply to every squad type.</p>

  <QuickSummary title="The Golden Rule — Main Squad First">
    <p><strong>Concentrate most of your resources into one squad.</strong> A dominant #1 squad carries you through most content. Your 2nd and 3rd squads only need to be “good enough.”</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>Core Principles (Apply to All Types)</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-base">Universal Rules</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li><strong>5 heroes per squad</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Mono-type only</strong> — All Tank, all Aircraft, or all Missile. The type bonus is too strong to ignore.</li>
        <li><strong>Positioning matters</strong> — Frontline draws fire. Backline DPS focuses the same target. Back-center is often targeted last.</li>
        <li><strong>Stars > Levels > Skills</strong> in ROI for most mid-game players — see <a href="/heroes" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">Heroes</a> for details.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-base">General Strategy</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li>Focus almost everything on your #1 squad until it is very strong.</li>
        <li>Many mid-game players successfully run two Tank squads before diversifying.</li>
        <li>Only start a serious second type once your main squad is reliably clearing the content you care about.</li>
        <li>UR heroes are the long-term goal, but well-built SSR/promotable heroes are excellent in mid-game.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Monica — The Elite Farmer</h2>
  <div class="quick-summary">
    <p>Slot Monica into Doom Elite rallies (lead or participate). Her skill gives a massive resource bonus on elites. 3–4 stars + moderate skill investment is usually enough.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Choose Your Path</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">Click into the specific type pages below — Tank has a detailed hero focus order; Aircraft and Missile are placeholders pending hero-type verification.</p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mt-4">
    <a href="/squad-building/tank" class="card p-5 block hover:border-[#f59e0b]/40">
      <div class="text-[#f59e0b] font-semibold mb-1">TANK</div>
      <div class="font-medium">Most popular mid-game choice</div>
      <div class="text-xs text-[#8a96b0] mt-2">Focus order: Kim → Stetmann → Williams → Murphy → Marshall</div>
    </a>
    <a href="/squad-building/aircraft" class="card p-5 block hover:border-[#f59e0b]/40">
      <div class="text-[#f59e0b] font-semibold mb-1">AIRCRAFT</div>
      <div class="font-medium">Counters Tank per the type triangle</div>
      <div class="text-xs text-[#8a96b0] mt-2">Guide in progress — pending verification</div>
    </a>
    <a href="/squad-building/missile" class="card p-5 block hover:border-[#f59e0b]/40">
      <div class="text-[#f59e0b] font-semibold mb-1">MISSILE</div>
      <div class="font-medium">Type triangle position — details TBD</div>
      <div class="text-xs text-[#8a96b0] mt-2">Guide in progress — pending verification</div>
    </a>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 text-xs text-[#5e6b85]">
    Community-made visual squad references — check the subreddit's guide threads — are a great supplement to hero focus orders and skill priorities.
  </div>
</Layout>
